# ── feat-wire-today-card-spawn-agent-buttons (#4124, PR-A) ──────────
#
# PERMANENT — agent-on-spawn-requested.ts is the Inngest function that
# consumes `agent.spawn.requested` events, resolves the operator's GitHub
# App install, then UPDATEs the three new acknowledgment columns on
# `action_sends` (write). Both surfaces need service-role:
#   - install read (#5470, ADR-044): the install is now resolved from the
#     operator's solo `workspaces` row via resolveInstallationIdForWorkspace
#     (handed the getServiceClient() instance) — no longer
#     `users.github_installation_id`, ahead of PR-2b's column drop. The
#     Inngest function runs with no cookie context (the event was signed by
#     INNGEST_SIGNING_KEY; founderId is server-derived from the dashboard
#     /send route's auth.getUser()). Tenant-JWT path would require
#     synthesizing a JWT for the founder, which the factory hook already
#     does for the GitHub App client; the canonical authenticated reader
#     (resolve_workspace_installation_id RPC) is REVOKE'd from service_role
#     AND gates on auth.uid(), so it returns NULL here — hence the distinct
#     service-role-safe resolver.
#   - action_sends UPDATE: the table's RLS substrate has owner-INSERT
#     and owner-SELECT policies only; UPDATE has no permissive policy
#     (default-deny). Migration 064's WORM-trigger reshape admits
#     UPDATEs that touch ONLY acknowledged_at + artifact_url +
#     failure_reason; service-role bypass is required to reach the
#     trigger gate.
# PR-B replaces the deterministic stub body with the Anthropic SDK
# leader-prompt loop; the service-role-allowlist entry persists across
# PR-A → PR-B because the SELECT + UPDATE surface is unchanged.
apps/web-platform/server/inngest/functions/agent-on-spawn-requested.ts

